After Steps→Blockly→Steps roundtrip, set_and_query commands degrade to write-only. The query half is permanently lost. Affects 4975 commands across all device families.
In stepToBlock.ts, set_and_query is converted to scpi_write (a Blockly block), dropping the query half. During Blockly→Steps export (blockToStep.ts), the block conversion returns 'write' type, not 'set_and_query', because the metadata was lost.
1) Preserve set_and_query metadata on imported scpi_write Blockly blocks. 2) Restore set_and_query type and params during Blockly→Steps export. 3) Generate write+query from Blockly when preserved metadata is present. 4) Added canary test (e2e/set-and-query-canary.spec.ts) gating this behavior.
