This affected the legacy screenshot template (MSO/DPO 5k/7k/70k series). The generated Python would send the literal command 'HARDCOPY:FORMAT ${format}' to the scope, which the scope would reject silently or misinterpret. The fix ensures the format variable (typically 'PNG') is properly interpolated into the generated code.
Generated Python code contains scope.write('HARDCOPY:FORMAT ${format}') which sends the literal string '${format}' to the scope instead of 'PNG'.
The generator used a JavaScript template literal backtick syntax inside a single-quoted string, so TypeScript didn't interpolate the variable. The ${format} was passed through literally to the Python output.
Changed to use proper TypeScript template literal with backticks and .toUpperCase(): code += `${device}.write('HARDCOPY:FORMAT ${format.toUpperCase()}')`
code += `${device}.write('HARDCOPY:FORMAT ${format}')\n`;
code += `${device}.write('HARDCOPY:FORMAT ${format.toUpperCase()}')\n`;

The fix uses setTimeout(() => { this.setFieldValue(this.currentBackend_, 'BACKEND'); }, 10) to update the field after Blockly's rendering cycle. A try-catch wraps the update since the field may not exist in all block states. This also triggers the color update (tm_devices blocks are purple/270, PyVISA blocks are green/120).
After importing XML with tm_devices backend, the connection block dropdown displays 'pyvisa' even though the internal mutation state correctly stores 'tm_devices'. Generated code uses wrong backend.
The domToMutation function correctly restored currentBackend_ from the mutation element, but it didn't update the dropdown BACKEND field in the UI. The field remained at its default value ('pyvisa').
Added setTimeout field update in both domToMutation and loadExtraState to update the dropdown after Blockly finishes rendering.
domToMutation(xmlElement) {
  this.currentBackend_ = xmlElement.getAttribute('current_backend') || 'pyvisa';
  // Field not updated! Shows 'pyvisa' in UI
}
domToMutation(xmlElement) {
  this.currentBackend_ = xmlElement.getAttribute('current_backend') || 'pyvisa';
  setTimeout(() => {
    try {
      if (this.getField('BACKEND')) {
        this.setFieldValue(this.currentBackend_, 'BACKEND');
      }
    } catch (e) {
      console.warn('Could not restore backend field value:', e);
    }
  }, 10);
}

