SCPI standard allows case-insensitive matching, but some Tektronix firmware versions have bugs where only the canonical mixed-case form is accepted. Using 'SEQuence' matches the form shown in programming manuals and works across MSO/DPO 5k/7k/70k and MSO 4/5/6 series.
scope.write('ACQUIRE:STOPAFTER SEQUENCE') works on some scopes but fails silently on others. Acquisition doesn't stop after single sequence.
Some Tektronix driver implementations expect mixed-case SCPI enum values (e.g., 'SEQuence') while the generator was using all-caps ('SEQUENCE').
Changed to use 'SEQuence' (mixed case) which is compatible with more driver implementations.
code += `${device}.commands.acquire.stopafter.write("SEQUENCE")\n`;
code += `${device}.commands.acquire.stopafter.write("SEQuence")\n`;

